rComments: Unwilling to hear the opinions of others. Brushed off when students voiced to her that they felt uncomfortable answering questions because of how she responded/reacted. Has a very 1900's approach to teaching. If you can take the course with another prof that would probably be best.

I've had her twice for 4th year courses and she's been very involved and enthusiastic. I find her lectures very interesting even when I'm not a fan of the subject matter. She's been extremely helpful concerning class assignments and graduate school applications. She's extremely fair so if you do poorly, it's your fault for not doing the work.
